reviews.text: It's an old restaurant. Food is great.. They have maintained the taste over the yrs.... Menu has improved.... They have a pretty Cool lounge bar also. Excellent place to visit either with family or friends... Evening reserve seats by 7 :00 pm or lunch by 12 :45 pm as sometime u will have to wait if u come after the same.

I went for lunch with my parent. Everything from Ambience, service and food was great. The food was not very costly and you can feel the authentic taste in every item you order. The service was really fast and all the staff were really polite. Will definitely go there again when I visit Cochin again

A historic  hotel in Ernakulam MG Road,  near Jose junction. 
     Used to visit this place for having lunch or dinner when I visit Cochin . Their menu has a wide spread of veg as well as as non veg options .  The lunch here is very famous and normally there is a waiting time and hence prior booking of table is advisable . Their Pearl spot fish fry and other non veg varieties are finger licking. 
   Need to admit that the  food they serve is fresh and really tasty. This place attracts a sophisticated crowd. They have a bar and good parking space as well. 
    But, Yes ..  their menu is a bit expensive but  they serve good portions . However the Service is not so great especially during peak hours.

Grand Hotel is an excellent option for dining. This is one place we keep coming back to whenever we come to Cochin. The customer service is exemplary and the food is delicious. The staff members always make it a point to make one's visit a memorable one. They have ample parking space with free valet service. From the doorman to the waiters, everyone knows how to keep up the class of the hotel. Outstanding!

We had lunch from here today. Definitely one of the best restaurant in Cochin. Price is on the higher side. But that is reasonable considering the quality and service they offer. Average cost per person is 400 and above. Fish curry meals and appam is a must try.
A delicious meal.  Really gracious and caring staff.  Not too intrusive.  A definite for our next visit to Edinburgh.  Highly recommended.  You will enjoy your visit.
Lovely food and service. Some of the food was only warm and not hot but overall the food was great. Would definitely return.

We just needed a place to escape from the cold and sleet. Ducked in for the heat, and stayed for the delicious Thai food and friendly service. Ordered the Pad Thai, vegetarian soup and were not disappointed.
Fabulous food, lovely service. Great for Coeliacs. Always a wonderful time here
Love this place so much. The best Thai food, cooked perfectly and great service. We always go here when we are in Edinburgh ♥
I’m always satisfied when I order from them!! And the delivery time is amazing!!!
Extra. Good. Pizza. And good deals. Too
Very good pizza and excellent customer service.

Traveling through Colorado we stayed at state park near by for 2 weeks. Had pizza from these guys 5 times and I have to admit they made great pizzas every single time. Pizza made to perfection. Best Domino's pizza I ever had. Give them a try you see what I mean
So good best pizza in the vally took kinda long but so worth it
The sandwich was a mess when i opened it up. Sauce was spilling out.
Good food, good service, good price

New management has done an amazing job taking this location to the next level.  Service is top notch and the food quality has improved exponentially!  Speed of service is noticably faster.  Definitely will be having more quick lunches here in the near future!
Agree! Food quality has gotten so much better since the old owner sold it.
Very friendly/polite staff!
